<div class='mid-column'>
<div class='category-header bg '>
<h4 class='post-category fg'><a href="http://www.splicetoday.com/politics-and-media">Politics & Media</a></h4>
<h4 class='post-date fg'>  
    Apr 24, 2012, 10:26AM  </h4>
</div>
<div id='right-column'>


<div class="discussion-column" id="discussion">
	<div class="category-header bg">
		<h4 class="post-category"><a href="/politics-and-media/equal-health-care-or-no-health-care-at-all" class="discussion">DISCUSSION</a></h4>
		
	</div>
	<ul class="comments" id="comments">
	  		
			<li>
<div class='comment-container' id='comment-16151' style='background-color:rgb(255,255,255)'>
<a name='comment-16151'></a>
<div class='user-info'>
<div class='screenname'>
<a href="http://www.splicetoday.com/profile/texan">Texan</a>
</div>
<div class='date'>Apr 24, 2012, 12:24PM</div>
</div>
<p>There is equal health care for all.  It is based on expense.  If one is willing/able to pay for it, it doesn't matter what race or religion they are.  This is called equality.  Why should someone who is unable or unwilling to pay the same amount as I do get the same level of health care?  How is that equality rather than favoring the unwilling/unable?</p>
</div>
</li>
<li>
<div class='comment-container' id='comment-16162' style='background-color:rgb(228,229,230)'>
<a name='comment-16162'></a>
<div class='user-info'>
<div class='screenname'>
<a href="http://www.splicetoday.com/profile/noah-berlatsky">Noah Berlatsky</a>
</div>
<div class='date'>Apr 25, 2012, 09:18AM</div>
</div>
<p>Texan, you seem confused about the meaning of equality.  Equality doesn't mean you are sorted out by whether or not you happen to be rich or poor.  It means people are treated equally on the basis of their being people, not on the basis of their income. Poverty is not a moral failing; people who can't afford to have their children's asthma treated don't deserve to have their kids die anymore than rich people deserve to have their kids die.  If you believe that that's true, you believe in equality. If you believe the poor kid should die (or "shouldn't get care", if you prefer), then you may believe in the market, or the prosperity gospel, but you don't believe in equality.  Simple as that.  </p>
